{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1061e068-7156-4529-89d3-8a81061432c7","content":"In .NET MAUI, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in your `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n    builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n    {\n#if ANDROID\n        events.AddAndroid(android => android\n            .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n            .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#elif IOS\n        events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n            .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n    });\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` is in the `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents` namespace.\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- `AddAndroid` exposes the full Android `Activity` lifecycle; `AddiOS` exposes `UIApplicationDelegate` events.\n- Other events like `OnResume`, `OnDestroy`, `WillEnterForeground`, etc. are available on the same builders.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"87438021-f996-423a-9864-fcc9cca892ff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI, specifically:\n- Android: OnPause/OnStop\n- iOS: DidEnterBackground\n\nThis is a knowledge question about .NET MAUI development. I can answer this directly without needing to search any codebase.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, you use the `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` method in your `MauiProgram.cs` to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events.","outputTokens":458,"requestId":"503B:28231D:1C4B58D:1F4E7EA:69FA904F"},"id":"d17903b4-5335-4374-afbf-312d1c5102c6","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:32.036Z","parentId":"cc5645a7-247f-4346-86d2-13f1da952ada"}
